{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require rainwater recovery for new builds and offer grants for older properties",
        "additional_details": "We're going to see more hosepipe bans and water shortages every year due to a range of factors:\r\n\r\nCirca 175k new properties being built every year, with the Government plan to increase to 300K\r\n\r\nNo new reservoirs built in 30 years\r\n\r\nClimate change is causing hotter, drier summers",
        "background": "The Government should require that all new builds have underground rainwater recovery systems installed. A grant scheme should also be set up. This could be funded by additional taxes on underperforming water companies, to help homeowners to retrofit on existing properties.",
